---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Research Workflow Guidebook
description: Choose a language, then move from setup to writing and GitHub-based collaboration.
pageClass: page-landing
---
<main>
  <section class="landing-hero">
    <div class="wrap hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-copy-block">
        <p class="eyebrow">Bilingual Guidebook</p>
        <h1>Choose a language, then build a research workflow that actually holds up.</h1>
        <p class="hero-copy">
          This site is being rebuilt as an editorial guidebook for researchers using LaTeX,
          VS Code, Git, and GitHub. The new structure keeps the public URLs stable while
          making the core bilingual path easier to maintain.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          {% for language in navigation.languages %}
            <a class="button {% if loop.first %}button-primary{% else %}button-secondary{% endif %}" href="{{ language.url }}">
              {{ language.label }}
            </a>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero-panel panel">
        <p class="eyebrow">Current Build</p>
        <h2>Eleventy migration in progress</h2>
        <p class="subtle">
          Core English and Korean paths are now being reorganized under shared templates,
          Markdown documents, and a search-ready static build.
        </p>
        {% if updates.latest %}
          <div class="update-chip">
            <span>{{ updates.latest.date }}</span>
            {% if updates.latest.url %}
              <a href="{{ updates.latest.url }}">{{ updates.latest.title }}</a>
            {% else %}
              <span>{{ updates.latest.title }}</span>
            {% endif %}
          </div>
        {% endif %}
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="editorial-band">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Route Map</p>
        <h2>Three sections, mirrored across English and Korean.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        {% for section in navigation.sections %}
          <article class="feature-card panel">
            <p class="card-kicker">{{ section.kicker.en }}</p>
            <h3>{{ section.title.en }}</h3>
            <p>{{ section.summary.en }}</p>
            <div class="link-row">
              <a href="{{ section.url.en }}">English</a>
              <a href="{{ section.url.ko }}">한국어</a>
            </div>
          </article>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="language-showcase">
    <div class="wrap language-grid">
      {% for language in navigation.languages %}
        <article class="language-card panel">
          <p class="eyebrow">{{ language.label }}</p>
          <h2>{% if language.code == "ko" %}한국어 진입 페이지{% else %}Language home{% endif %}</h2>
          <p class="subtle">{{ language.summary }}</p>
          <a class="text-link" href="{{ language.url }}">
            {% if language.code == "ko" %}한국어 홈으로 이동{% else %}Enter the English home{% endif %}
          </a>
        </article>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
